covered: Valid Request: Happy path scenarios cover successful retrieval with required path parameter.
Empty Response: TC06 and TC24 cover empty results when no bundles match or database is empty.
Pagination: Offset/limit scenarios tested (TC02, TC07, TC08) and large data scenarios (TC19, TC26) addressing pagination boundaries.
Query Parameters: Coverage across combinations of offset, limit, audit, and extra parameters (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC09–TC12, TC18).
Authorization: Missing and invalid authentication token scenarios (TC13, TC14).
Error Handling: Diverse error responses including 400 for bad input (TC09–TC12), 500 (TC16), 503 (TC15), and 504 timeout (TC25).
Performance/Scale: Large data volume tests (TC19, TC26) and concurrency (TC20).
Audit detail: FULL/MINIMAL audit parameter coverage (TC03, TC04).
Robustness to unexpected input: Extra query parameter handling (TC18).
gaps: Rate limiting/throttling tests (e.g., 429 Too Many Requests).
Tests validating response headers beyond body contents (e.g., content-type, server headers).
Boundary tests for searchKey length and more exotic/unicode inputs beyond basic cases.
UI accessibility tests (TC22) are UI-focused; API coverage could be clarified or separated.
recommendations: Add rate limiting tests and verify 429 responses under high request rates.
Add tests asserting caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and proper cache behavior.
Add 403-only authorization tests to cover insufficient-permission scenarios.
Add edge-case tests for searchKey length boundaries and extended character sets/unicode handling.
Clarify scope for UI accessibility tests or separate them from API-focused coverage.
